  <h2 class="no-margin subsection-header" data-anchor="legend-items">
    Legend Items
    <small class="header-link"><LinkTo @route="index" @query={{hash anchor="legend-items"}}>{{fa-icon "link"}}</LinkTo></small>
  </h2>
  <h4 class="dark-gray text-weight-normal">labs-ui/legend-items</h4>
  <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x">
    <div class="cell large-5">
      <p>The <code>legend-items</code> component does not yield any content directly. It simply loops through the array of legend objects and passes each one to the <code>labs-ui/legend-item</code> component.</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <td>Param</td>
            <td>Type</td>
            <td>Default</td>
            <td>Description</td>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong><pre>items</pre></strong></td>
            <td>object</td>
            <td>null</td>
            <td>Structured data, array of legend objects (required)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="cell large-7">
      <pre><code>&#123;{labs-ui/legend-items items=layerGroup.legend.items}}</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>


  <hr>


  <h2 class="no-margin subsection-header" data-anchor="legend-item">
    Legend Item
    <small class="header-link"><LinkTo @route="index" @query={{hash anchor="legend-item"}}>{{fa-icon "link"}}</LinkTo></small>
  </h2>
  <h4 class="dark-gray text-weight-normal">labs-ui/legend-item</h4>
  <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x">
    <div class="cell large-5">
      <p>The <code>legend-item</code> component is called by the <code>each</code> loop in the <code>legend-items</code> component. It renders a label (required), tooltip, and icon.</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <td>Param</td>
            <td>Type</td>
            <td>Default</td>
            <td>Description</td>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong><pre>item</pre></strong></td>
            <td>object</td>
            <td>null</td>
            <td>Structured data, legend object (required)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="cell large-7">
      <pre><code>&#123;{labs-ui/legend-item item=model.exampleItem}}</code></pre>
      {{labs-ui/legend-item item=model.exampleItem}}
    </div>
  </div>


  <hr>


  <h2 class="no-margin subsection-header" data-anchor="legend-icon">
    Legend Icon
    <small class="header-link"><LinkTo @route="index" @query={{hash anchor="legend-icon"}}>{{fa-icon "link"}}</LinkTo></small>
  </h2>
  <h4 class="dark-gray text-weight-normal">labs-ui/legend-icon</h4>
  <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x">
    <div class="cell large-5">
      <p>The <code>legend-icon</code> component renders a layered stack of icons. The <code>icon.type</code> can be <code>line</code>, <code>rectangle</code>, or <code>fa-icon</code>, and determines if the layers are made of SVGs or Font Awesome icons. The <code>icon.layers</code> array of objects describes each of the layers in the stack &mdash; e.g. a dark red line over a thicker transparent pink line. </p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <td>Param</td>
            <td>Type</td>
            <td>Default</td>
            <td>Description</td>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong><pre>icon</pre></strong></td>
            <td>object</td>
            <td>null</td>
            <td>Structured data,  (required)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="cell large-7">
      <pre><code>&#123;{labs-ui/legend-icon icon=model.exampleItem.icon}}</code></pre>
      <span class="legend-item">{{labs-ui/legend-icon icon=model.exampleItem.icon}}</span>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

